cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about measuring the compositional generalization ability of machine learning models on a natural language question answering dataset. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the correlation between compound divergence and accuracy, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
